# ================================================================================
# This Area Of Code Is: Git Attributes Configuration
# Explanation: Tells Git how to handle different file types - line endings,
# merge behavior, and which files to treat as binary (not diffable).
# In Other Words: Settings for how Git should treat different file types.
# ================================================================================

# This Area Of Code Is: Auto Line Endings
# Explanation: Automatically handles line endings (LF vs CRLF) based on the
# operating system. Prevents "whole file changed" issues between Mac/Windows.
# In Other Words: Makes line endings work on both Mac and Windows automatically.
* text=auto

# This Area Of Code Is: Source Code Files
# Explanation: Forces consistent LF line endings for code files regardless of OS.
# In Other Words: Code files always use Unix-style line endings.
*.js text eol=lf
*.css text eol=lf
*.html text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf

# This Area Of Code Is: Documentation Files
# Explanation: Treats markdown and text files as text with auto line endings.
# In Other Words: Text files get proper line ending handling.
*.md text
*.txt text

# This Area Of Code Is: Binary Files (Images)
# Explanation: Marks image files as binary so Git doesn't try to diff them.
# In Other Words: Don't try to compare image files line-by-line.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.svg binary

# This Area Of Code Is: Binary Files (Video/Audio)
# Explanation: Marks video and audio files as binary (large, not diffable).
# In Other Words: Video files are binary blobs, not text.
*.mp4 binary
*.webm binary
*.mp3 binary
*.wav binary

# This Area Of Code Is: Font Files
# Explanation: Font files are binary assets.
# In Other Words: Font files are binary.
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary

# This Area Of Code Is: Archive Files
# Explanation: Compressed archives are binary.
# In Other Words: Zip files are binary.
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
